{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8026", "repo": "rails", "body": "If we really want to make sure that `ENV['RAILS_ENV']` is set, I think we should just add a `before_configuration` block to some railtie/application/bootstrap class.\r\n\r\nThis way we're explicitly setting the env var right at boot time, and not relying on `Rails.env` being called.\r\n\r\nI mean something like this: `config.before_configuration { ENV['RAILS_ENV'] ||= Rails.env.to_s }`.\r\n\r\nWDYT?", "_id": {"$oid": "523db285bd354364b9009338"}, "issue_id": 8026, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9795108", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8026#issuecomment-9795108", "updated_at": "2012-10-25T21:35:13Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva", "login": "exviva", "gravatar_id": "56c0f984e7a1cccbd5ea165ef310ba4f", "html_url": "https://github.com/exviva", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/56c0f984e7a1cccbd5ea165ef310ba4f?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa77d299ee00dfee2de17de8fcd02c69a.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 80070, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-10-25T21:35:13Z", "id": 9795108, "owner": "rails"}
